parliamentary monarch. In

the meantime, the Tsar sent most of the Russian Baltic Fleet to
retake Port Arthur from the Japanese. Two thirds of the ships
were sunk by the Japanese Combined Fleet in the Battle of
Tsushima in May 1905. In October 1905, Tsar Nicolas II
acquiesced to the formation of an elected parliament, the
Duma, and the establishment of a constitutional monarchy.
However, he soon reneged granting full oversight powers to this


